gui.weaponmaster.page1_0: DON'T WORRY THIS GUIDE IS VERY CONCISE LOL
gui.weaponmaster.page1_1: As you might guess, you need two things to start with the weapon mod
gui.weaponmaster.page1_5: You'll use it to redeem your weapon choice and upgrade/customize.
gui.weaponmaster.page1_6: Make it or look it up as below, or steal from a friend. Your pack may vary for balancing.
gui.weaponmaster.page2_0: To pick your weapon, Craft a Weapon Kit and right-click to open the selection menu.
gui.weaponmaster.page2_5: These are classified as Agile and Superheavy, Sweeping and Precise.
gui.weaponmaster.page2_6: All weapons use unique hit detection, Sweeping always swings in a fan, dealing full damage. Precision hits straight ahead only, but pierces and deals more damage.
gui.weaponmaster.page2_7: Agile weapons have high swing speeds, and then Superheavy deals more damage and range.
gui.weaponmaster.page2_8: Broadswords are Agile Sweepers, for reliable control.
gui.weaponmaster.page2_9: Broadswords are Agile Sweepers, for reliable control.
gui.weaponmaster.page3_0: Scythes are Superheavy Sweepers, to hit massive crowds for burst damage.
gui.weaponmaster.page3_1: Polearms are Superheavy Precisions, for killing one guy and every dude behind him extremely hard.
gui.weaponmaster.page3_2: Picking something you will stick with early in is decently important, as of the following.
gui.weaponmaster.page3_3: Once you have it, it will be broken at first. Take it to the Studio to fix. Any time it 'breaks' you can just do this again.
gui.weaponmaster.page3_9: The Studio uses this Radial Dial to select the submenu for editing and selecting various weapon characteristics.
gui.weaponmaster.page4_5: Your item can't be enchanted, but it can Level. Select the bar of the stat you want to contribute to and it will level with use.
gui.weaponmaster.page5_0: When you fill a level bar, as seen in your weapon tooltip HUD, the level counter with increment, and the next time you open the Studio with it, the Unlocks Menu opens.
gui.weaponmaster.page5_1: You get a random set each time you level.
gui.weaponmaster.page5_2: Abilities are Per Weapon! More on those later.
gui.weaponmaster.page5_3: Part Blueprints though, you remember how to apply them Permanently. In case you somehow lose your weapon, or want to upgrade your unlucky friend's item.
gui.weaponmaster.page5_4: Per level, you can pick ONE Ability Unlock, and THREE Part Unlocks.
gui.weaponmaster.page6_0: Repairing your weapon is 'free' in resources, and instead costs your precious time.
gui.weaponmaster.page6_1: Completely cover it with the high-grit polish, wipe it off with good pressure, then just flip and repeat.
gui.weaponmaster.page6_2: If you got everything properly, you'll see it shine.
gui.weaponmaster.page7_0: Abilities are extremely powerful ways to customize how you fight.
gui.weaponmaster.page7_1: Select and confirm in the Abilities tab, and use them by pressing right-click in mainhand.
gui.weaponmaster.page7_2: Abilities are Cooldown based per-similar type.
gui.weaponmaster.page7_3: You can chain different abilities across weapons together, but they will stack their cooldowns!
gui.weaponmaster.page7_4: Their use is extremely varied, so experiment as you unlock.
gui.weaponmaster.page8_0: - You keep your weapon on death (unless config says otherwise) but it completely breaks.
gui.weaponmaster.page8_1: - Once your Level is displayed green in the tooltip HUD, it will not gain any more benefits from leveling.
gui.weaponmaster.page8_2: - You can keep leveling anyway to earn Prestige, and keep getting unlocks. Prestige is to show-off. 1 P-Star p. 10 Levels
gui.weaponmaster.page8_3: - If you are prone to butterfingers, please change your throw bind so you don't lose your weapon, lmao
gui.weaponmaster.page8_4: - Place your Studio up against a block to show the cloth layer for it.
gui.weaponmaster.page8_5: - XP curves gradually make it less lucrative over time. Switch up your stat contributions!
gui.weaponmaster.page8_6: - If you are using this mod in a PVP pack, I would suggest asking God for mercy in your next encounter.

ability.weaponmaster.buster.confession: Hello there fellow dev! Desian here. You're either reading this making an addon mod (I'm sorry) or making a resource pack (I'm *really* sorry). Either way, I'm not here to help you! (again, sorry). But look, I need to tell you about something about buster. Originally, what would eventually become resist and smokescreen was a collection of single potion effect abilities, labelled pot_resist, post_speed and pot_invis. Now, obviously, being the funny jokester I am, I also made a pot_buster. It didn't *do* anything but it was very funny for a bit. Now, like any self-respecting programmer I don't know when to drop a joke, so it got a really basic implementation, you literally just jumped up and anyone you hit got knocked down. It sucked and I fully intended to remove it. Anyway, a lot of things got shuffled around during testing, including the removal of the pot_ abilities in favour of the more flavourful variants we have now. This brought a little too much attention to buster and insted of doing the smart thing of going 'yeah gimme a sec i'll remove that' I went along with Forset and actually remade it into a proper ability! This took weeks! It ***STILL*** has netcode issues! Anyway, absolutely no part of the original joke exists in the final build otherwise so I kinda felt like I *needed* to document it in some form, y'know?
ability.weaponmaster.buster.confession.2: Hi dev. Forset here. Yeah, unfortunately that one's my fault. Honestly, I just really want to see a video of someone using this ability on another player if the mod spreads around into enough packs. That's kind of my only motivation and that I thought it was a hilarious anti-air. Unlike Desian, I am not sorry.
ability.weaponmaster.buster.confession.3: Desian again, do want to clarify that nether of us consulted the other when adding these to the lang file, i'm pretty sure we're just doing a bit here at this point.

part.rapier_guard_dice.confession: Hello! Desian again! This hilt has a great story attached to it. Ok so, I'm assuming you know what psudorandom numbers are. Well, for a time our creative tab had this weird problem where the hilt of the rapiers would not change for like 20 different generations and Forset's submitting this bug report to me utterly confused. I, of course, recognise this immediately and correctly just go 'yeah maths sucks like that sometimes, we can do literally anything to fix this' so like, *obviously* I do the silliest thing and dedicate an entire new hilt to fixing this one in a million bug that could've been fixed way simpler with like, a single line of code. Hence, the rigged dice (it is actually rigged! I'm very proud of it.).
